Hezbollah's Secretary-General Responds to Calls for Disarming the Party

### English Text Summary:
Sheikh Naeem Qassem, the Secretary-General of Hezbollah, responded to calls for disarming the party, asserting that they will confront anyone attempting to disarm them or attack the party. He emphasized that the weaponry of the resistance has granted freedom to their people and liberated their homeland. In a televised address, he stated that Hezbollah is not weak and is prepared for confrontation, referencing their past resistance against Israel. Qassem claimed that the ceasefire agreement was a result of Hezbollah's resilience, suggesting that without their steadfastness, Israel would have continued its aggression.

